Namibia  plans to raise 10.1 billion
Namibian dollars ($1.5 billion) in debt this year, of which 2.7
billion Namibian dollars would be raised outside the country,
Saara Kuungongelwa-Amadhila, the countryâ€™s finance minister,
told investors in Windhoek, the capital, today.  The money to be raised is part of a three-year program to
raise 26.4 billion Namibian dollars, she said.  The country will also sell retail and inflation-linked
bonds for the first time, she said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
